author: Justin Wilson
title: UCF Sprit Teams Set for Nationals This Weekend - UCF Athletics - Official Athletics Website
text:
The UCF spirit teams will compete at the 2025 College Cheerleading and Dance Team National Championship this weekend. The competition will be held at the ESPN Wide World of Sports Complex from Friday, Jan. 17 through Sunday, Jan. 19.
UCF’s cheer team will be competing in the division 1A coed and gameday events. Last year, the Knights claimed their fourth national title in the coed division and first since 2020, after also earning the top spot in 2007 and 2003. UCF won the 2019 crown in the gameday division.
After recording its best finish in the hip hop division in 2024 with a fifth-place finish, the Knights’ dance team will compete in the division 1A hip hop and 1A jazz. Last year, the dance team placed seventh in hip hop and 14th in jazz. This was the second year in a row that the team finished seventh in hip hop, marking their best finish in team history.
UCF and LSU were the only two programs to advance to the finals in coed cheer, jazz and hip hop a season ago.
CHAMPIONSHIP SCHEDULE
Friday 1/17 1:07pm Division 1A Cheer Gameday Semi Finals
6:45-7:55pm Division 1A Cheer Gameday Finals
9pm Division IA Dance Jazz Prelims
Saturday 1/18 12:38pm Division 1A Cheer Co-Ed Semi Finals
8:48pm Division 1A Dance Hip Hop Semi Finals
3-7pm Division 1A Dance Jazz Semi Finals
Sunday 1/19 2:30-3:30pm Division 1A Cheer Co-Ed Finals
4-5pm Division 1A Dance Jazz Finals
7:30-9pm Division 1A Dance Hip Hop Finals
Single day tickets can be purchased at the Disney Wide World of Sports Box office on the day of the event or by clicking HERE.
The competition can also be seen live on VarsityTV.com
